{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3185729,"name":"Yi Cheng","username":"Yee0","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/y/848f3c/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-04-10T22:19:59.079Z","cooked":"

When we were at NE District Champs, our team saw that we had some conflicting firmware on our motors, so we tried to open Phoenix Tuner to update the motor we recently replaced but found that Phoenix Tuner refused to open. It worked fine the previous week, and we didn’t do anything to the software or computer, it just stopped working. Later that day, I tried restarting the computer, deleting it, and redownloading it over and over again to no avail.

We have a spare laptop to use, so it should be fine for now, I was just wondering if anyone had any ideas as to why this is happening and how I can fix it?

(Also, thank you to the teams who let us borrow their laptop at District Champs!)

Unfortunately, there is a Windows bug that prevents one of our required dependencies from auto-updating, causing the symptoms above.

Download the latest offline installer from Releases · CrossTheRoadElec/Phoenix-Releases · GitHub, install, and Tuner should be fixed. You also be able to update from the Windows Store like normal.
